questionGroupSummary.name: Personal Info
questionGroupSummary.description: Sharing personal information can significantly impact the likelihood of you becoming a victim of identity theft or fraud.

questionGroupSummary.name: Technology & Internet
questionGroupSummary.description: The technology, software, devices, and platforms you utilize to access the internet are all easy identity theft targets. These vulnerabilities could put your information at risk.

questionGroupSummary.name: Home & Travel
questionGroupSummary.description: The more insurers and services you use at home and while traveling, the more likely you may become a victim of identity theft or fraud.

questionGroupSummary.name: Social Media
questionGroupSummary.description: The more social media accounts you have, the more information you share, which increases the likelihood of becoming a victim of identity theft or fraud.

questionGroupSummary.name: Shopping
questionGroupSummary.description: Providing us information about where you shop and what types of services you subscribe to helps us evaluate your risk of identity theft.

questionGroupSummary.name: Healthcare
questionGroupSummary.description: Healthcare companies, which collect and store very personal information, could become victims of cybercrime. Tell us which insurers you have policies with to help us assess your risk of identity theft.

questionGroupSummary.name: Finance
questionGroupSummary.description: Your risk of identity theft may increase depending on the number and types of bank accounts and credit cards you have.
